{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:12:47.556Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"oaq8vtto","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md:1-150","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Platform: Phase 3 Interactive Tools & Phase 4 FastAPI Backend Contracts\n  2 | \n  3 | This document establishes the strategic architectural interface between the high-fidelity client-side interactive tools built in **Phase 3** and the future enterprise-grade, high-performance **FastAPI backend (Phase 4)**. \n  4 | \n  5 | ---\n  6 | \n  7 | ## 1. Executive Architecture Overview\n  8 | \n  9 | In Phase 3, GFF AI delivers an **unmatched, premium, frontend-only interactive suite** spanning the *Build Hub* workspace. These tools (Blueprint Builder, Readiness Assessment, ROI Calculator, RFP/Proposal Builder, Client Sandbox, Foundry Studio workflow canvas, and Agent Marketplace) run fully on client-side state machine architectures to maximize fluid responsiveness, respect data privacy boundaries, and ensure flawless offline capability during presentation.\n 10 | \n 11 | In Phase 4, these interactive tools will transition from local state management to a robust, containerized Python **FastAPI backend**. This migration will enable secure multi-user collaboration, real-time agent execution orchestration, persistent database storage, and integrations with enterprise identity providers.\n 12 | \n 13 | ### 1.1. Hybrid Architecture Topology\n 14 | \n 15 | ```\n 16 | +---------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 17 | |                               CLIENT BROWSER (Next.js)                          |\n 18 | |                                                                                 |\n 19 | |  +-------------------------+   +------------------------+   +----------------+  |\n 20 | |  |  Build Hub Workspace    |   |  Interactive Tools UI  |   | Local Storage  |  |\n 21 | |  |  (React/Next.js/Framer) |   |  (React Hook Form/Zod) |   | & Session Cache|  |\n 22 | |  +------------+------------+   +-----------+------------+   +--------+-------+  |\n 23 | |               |                            |                         |          |\n 24 | +---------------|----------------------------|-------------------------|----------+\n 25 |                 | SECURE TLS (HTTPS)         |                         | Sync\n 26 |                 |                            |                         | (Future Phase 4)\n 27 |                 v                            v                         v\n 28 | +--------------------------------------------+------------------------------------+\n 29 | |                             FUTURE FASTAPI BACKEND SERVICES                     |\n 30 | |                                                                                 |\n 31 | |   +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+  |\n 32 | |   |                       API Router & Gateway Controller                    |  |\n 33 | |   |         - Pydantic Input Validation      - JWT/OTP Security Middleware   |  |\n 34 | |   |         - SlowAPI Rate Limiter           - CORS Policy Manager           |  |\n 35 | |   +----+--------------------+--------------------+--------------------+----+  |\n 36 | |        |                    |                    |                    |         |\n 37 | |        v                    v                    v                    v         |\n 38 | |  +-----------+        +-----------+        +-----------+        +------------+  |\n 39 | |  | Cache     |        | Database  |        | Object    |        | Email /    |  |\n 40 | |  | (Redis)   |        | (Postgres)|        | Store     |        | OTP Engine |  |\n 41 | |  | - OTPs    |        | - Users   |        | (AWS S3)  |        | (SES /     |  |\n 42 | |  | - Session |        | - Proposls|        | - PDFs    |        | SendGrid)  |  |\n 43 | |  | - RateLim |        | - Flows   |        | - Configs |        | - Auth     |  |\n 44 | |  +-----------+        +-----------+        +-----------+        +------------+  |\n 45 | +---------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 46 | ```\n 47 | \n 48 | ---\n 49 | \n 50 | ## 2. Phase 3 Interactive Tools Status\n 51 | \n 52 | The table below catalogs what has been fully implemented inside the Next.js workspace for Phase 3, specifying where the boundary of \"frontend-only simulation\" lies and what operations will be handled by the FastAPI microservices in Phase 4.\n 53 | \n 54 | | Interactive Tool | Phase 3 Frontend Capability | Future Phase 4 Backend Integration |\n 55 | | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n 56 | | **Blueprint Builder** | Interactive multi-step journey, dynamic architecture node rendering, PDF download simulation, client-side share link creation. | Persistent storage, real-time database generation, AI-generated custom system components, PDF generation in Python. |\n 57 | | **Readiness Assessment** | Comprehensive 5-category evaluation matrix, scoring weights, remediation checklists, local results storage. | Enterprise aggregation, comparative industry benchmarking, administrative audit trails. |\n 58 | | **ROI Calculator** | Real-time strategic financial formula processor (TCO, NPV, Payback, FTE reallocation) with visual charts. | High-fidelity model adjustment, customizable exportable spreadsheets, corporate database storage. |\n 59 | | **Proposal Builder**| Custom RFP requirements intake, step-by-step modular timeline constructor, proposal compiler. | Large Language Model (LLM) customized RFP generation, direct client PDF render pipeline, collaborative drafting. |\n 60 | | **Client Sandbox** | Interactive shell with terminal output simulation, sample developer tasks, live log visualizer. | Dockerized ephemeral execution environments, actual command execution, sandboxed Python interpreters. |\n 61 | | **Foundry Studio** | Drag-and-drop multi-agent workflow DAG designer, canvas node interaction, cyclical validation checks. | DAG execution engine, Celery task broker synchronization, deployment manifest compiles. |\n 62 | | **Agent Marketplace** | Filterable catalog of pre-configured enterprise agent definitions, installation toggles. | Real-time agent downloads, version control, third-party author portal uploads, licensing, secure keys. |\n 63 | \n 64 | ---\n 65 | \n 66 | ## 3. Phase 4 Target Backend System Architecture\n 67 | \n 68 | To ensure premium execution, the FastAPI backend will utilize a robust architectural stack:\n 69 | \n 70 | 1. **FastAPI Framework (Python 3.12+)**: Leveraging high-performance `asyncio` for scalable multi-connection handling. FastAPI natively exports strict OpenAPI schemas via Redoc or Swagger.\n 71 | 2. **Relational Database (PostgreSQL 16+)**: Managed relational store utilizing SQLAlchemy ORM or SQLModel. Houses user credentials, enterprise workflows, generated proposals, audit histories, and compliance records.\n 72 | 3. **In-Memory Cache (Redis 7+)**: Used for high-speed rate-limiting, short-term OTP validation tokens, and secure JWT blacklist/session states.\n 73 | 4. **AWS S3 or S3-Compatible Object Storage**: Enterprise repository for archiving dynamically compiled PDF blueprints, corporate agreements, custom proposals, and downloadable sandbox snapshots. \n 74 | 5. **No AWS or Cloud Credentials in Phase 3**: In compliance with security policies, all cloud, database, and SMTP services remain abstractly represented via strict, un-hydrated configuration variables.\n 75 | 6. **Authentication Flow**: Completely passwordless, secure, enterprise-tailored One-Time Password (OTP) validation delivered to business emails. Supports corporate domains only, utilizing an abstract communication dispatcher layer (SES, Mailgun, or SendGrid).\n 76 | \n 77 | ---\n 78 | \n 79 | ## 4. FastAPI API Endpoint Catalog\n 80 | \n 81 | This section contains the official HTTP specifications for the target FastAPI endpoints. All endpoints assume a baseline prefix of `/api`. All JSON schemas represent strict Pydantic structures.\n 82 | \n 83 | ---\n 84 | \n 85 | ### 4.1. POST /api/blueprint/generate\n 86 | \n 87 | **Purpose**: Persistently stores and generates an advanced strategic enterprise AI architecture blueprint based on target constraints, compliance frameworks, and infrastructure choices.\n 88 | \n 89 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n 90 | *   **Path**: `/api/blueprint/generate`\n 91 | *   **Security Requirement**: Optional Session Authentication (registers draft anonymously or links to authenticated user profile).\n 92 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n 93 |     ```json\n 94 |     {\n 95 |       \"company_name\": \"Acme Global Enterprise\",\n 96 |       \"industry\": \"Financial Services\",\n 97 |       \"compliance_frameworks\": [\"SOC2\", \"HIPAA\", \"EU_AI_ACT\"],\n 98 |       \"data_residency\": \"EU_WEST\",\n 99 |       \"infrastructure_preference\": \"Sovereign_Cloud\",\n100 |       \"deployment_scale\": \"Enterprise_Wide\",\n101 |       \"selected_capabilities\": [\n102 |         \"Knowledge_Graph_Mesh\",\n103 |         \"Autonomous_Agent_Orchestrators\",\n104 |         \"Governance_Guardrails\"\n105 |       ],\n106 |       \"budget_tier\": \"Premium_Enterprise\"\n107 |     }\n108 |     ```\n109 | *   **Response Payload (`[ILLUSTRATIVE MOCK]`)**:\n110 |     ```json\n111 |     {\n112 |       \"blueprint_id\": \"blu_908f7e21-3a0c-4991-88b1-38f7e1b99c72\",\n113 |       \"created_at\": \"2026-06-27T10:30:15Z\",\n114 |       \"compliance_rating\": 98.4,\n115 |       \"estimated_deployment_time_weeks\": 12,\n116 |       \"recommended_architecture_nodes\": [\n117 |         {\n118 |           \"id\": \"node-1\",\n119 |           \"label\": \"GFF AI Sovereign Edge\",\n120 |           \"type\": \"infrastructure\",\n121 |           \"status\": \"critical\"\n122 |         },\n123 |         {\n124 |           \"id\": \"node-2\",\n125 |           \"label\": \"Agent Orchestration Mesh\",\n126 |           \"type\": \"orchestrator\",\n127 |           \"status\": \"active\"\n128 |         }\n129 |       ],\n130 |       \"generated_narrative\": \"Based on financial service constraints, GFF AI prescribes a secure, sovereign-hosted multi-agent cluster backed by real-time governance guardrails.\",\n131 |       \"pdf_download_url\": \"https://assets.gff.ai/blueprints/blu_908f7e21_export.pdf\"\n132 |     }\n133 |     ```\n134 | *   **Error Responses**:\n135 |     *   `400 Bad Request`: If empty inputs or incompatibilities exist in selected frameworks.\n136 |     *   `422 Unprocessable Entity`: Validation failure on Pydantic models (e.g. invalid string enum in `data_residency`).\n137 | \n138 | ---\n139 | \n140 | ### 4.2. POST /api/assessment/score\n141 | \n142 | **Purpose**: Takes complex multi-dimensional AI readiness assessments from the client, calculates overall and categorical readiness scores, and maps out targeted remediation paths.\n143 | \n144 | *   **HTTP Method**: `POST`\n145 | *   **Path**: `/api/assessment/score`\n146 | *   **Security Requirement**: Public / Anonymous Access with optional JWT Session linking.\n147 | *   **Request Payload Schema (JSON)**:\n148 |     ```json\n149 |     {\n150 |       \"assessment_session_id\": \"sess_89a71b3e\",","success":true}],"durationMs":8}}
