egistry of client organizations under management. Admins can audit each client's SLA compliance matrices and allocate/revoke hardware nodes dynamically.\n+192: *   **Infrastructure Model Deployer**: Oversees regional orchestrator loads and schedules memory pruning routines.\n+193: *   **Global IAM & Users Hub**: Enables direct oversight over client employees and internal GFF staff clearance level assignments.\n+194: \n+195: ---\n+196: \n+197: ## 7. Local Mock Data Structures\n+198: \n+199: All dashboards, tables, and telemetry parameters consume structured, static mock structures modeled to mimic real-world SQL schemas and JSON payloads.\n+200: \n+201: ### 7.1. Node Cluster Database Model (`ClusterNode`)\n+202: Represents the dedicated hardware nodes allocated to running models.\n+203: ```typescript\n+204: export interface ClusterNode {\n+205:   id: string;\n+206:   nodeId: string;       // e.g., \"RETAIL-CORE-A1\"\n+207:   client: string;       // e.g., \"Sovereign Retail Group\"\n+208:   status: \"active\" | \"warning\" | \"stable\" | \"decoupled\";\n+209:   load: string;         // e.g., \"42.1%\"\n+210:   uptime: string;       // e.g., \"99.998%\"\n+211: }\n+212: ```\n+213: \n+214: ### 7.2. Invoice Ledger Model (`Invoice`)\n+215: Used to render SLA cost auditing grids.\n+216: ```typescript\n+217: export interface Invoice {\n+218:   id: string;           // e.g., \"GFF-INV-2026-004\"\n+219:   date: string;\n+220:   dueDate: string;\n+221:   amount: string;\n+222:   status: \"Settled\" | \"Overdue\" | \"Pending Handshake\";\n+223:   computationalEpochs: number;\n+224:   tokenConsumption: string;\n+225:   pdfHash: string;      // Simulated SHA-256 validation checksum\n+226: }\n+227: ```\n+228: \n+229: ### 7.3. Incident SLA Ticket Model (`SupportTicket`)\n+230: Models mission-critical operator-support pipelines.\n+231: ```typescript\n+232: export interface SupportTicket {\n+233:   id: string;           // e.g., \"SLA-9102\"\n+234:   subject: string;\n+235:   severity: \"CRITICAL (L1)\" | \"HIGH (L2)\" | \"MEDIUM (L3)\";\n+236:   status: \"Resolved\" | \"Investigating\" | \"Awaiting Handshake\";\n+237:   updatedAt: string;\n+238:   assignedOperator: string;\n+239: }\n+240: ```\n+241: \n+242: ---\n+243: \n+244: ## 8. Frontend-Only Scope & Limitations\n+245: \n+246: As configured by Phase 4 architectural guardrails, the portal and admin interfaces are **strictly client-side representations**. \n+247: \n+248: ### 8.1. State Containment\n+249: *   **Local Storage Volatility**: All state changes (modified agent prompts, newly simulated support tickets, model toggles, profile adjustments) are stored either in localized React state or synced temporarily to `localStorage`. Refreshing the browser window resets all database metrics to their baseline template configurations.\n+250: *   **Mock Verification Gateway**: No actual network connections are initiated to backend databases, server hypervisors, or identity engines. Authentication succeeds automatically on valid role-selection templates.\n+251: *   **Abstract Identity Delivery**: Email OTP inputs bypass actual verification. Clicking the \"Send OTP Code\" button triggers local terminal animations listing simulated SMTP dispatch routes, rather than delivering a real code.\n+252: \n+253: \n+254: \n+255: \n```","success":true},"durationMs":2}}
