reams & WebSockets\n+404: *   Set up FastAPI WebSocket router paths to serve real-time hardware telemetry and audit messages.\n+405: *   Incorporate server loops to pipe simulated server load and uptime logs into active sockets.\n+406: *   *Verification Matrix*: Replace the static timer loops in `/portal/dashboard` with direct event listeners reading from active WS sockets.\n+407: \n+408: ### Sprint 4: Sandbox Workspace & Model Enclave API controllers\n+409: *   Build control parameters for client workspaces, enabling users to edit agent configurations, save custom prompts, and toggle active LLM model engines.\n+410: *   Incorporate database persistence to store prompt variations, preventing reset on browser reloads.\n+411: \n+412: ### Sprint 5: S3 Storage & SMTP Email Gates\n+413: *   Establish AWS SDK (boto3) configurations with zero access credentials committed to source control (utilizing AWS IAM Role profiles or container environment injectors).\n+414: *   Construct SMTP email delivery handlers using secure SMTP / AWS SES.\n+415: *   Enable real passwordless verification and file downloads on `/portal/documents`.\n+416: \n+417: ### Sprint 6: billing, Stripe webhooks, and Cryptographic Signatures\n+418: *   Develop usage-tracking cron workers that aggregate computational hours.\n+419: *   Set up Stripe subscription hooks to synchronize invoice generation.\n+420: *   Build the PDF ledger builder with cryptographic signatures, satisfying corporate compliance guidelines.\n+421: \n+422: \n+423: \n+424: \n+425: \n+426: \n```","success":true},"durationMs":1}}
