{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:17:09.805Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"inhec0gg","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/PHASE_4_LOGIN_ADMIN_CLIENT_PORTAL.md:1-100","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Platform: Phase 4 Secure Login, Client Portal & Admin Oversight Console\n  2 | \n  3 | This document establishes the strategic, enterprise-grade architecture, implementation details, and future backend contracts for **Phase 4** of the GFF AI Platform. \n  4 | \n  5 | In Phase 4, GFF AI delivers an advanced, premium, **high-fidelity presentation interface** representing the ultimate Sovereign Operating System for enterprise AI governance. This frontend is carefully designed with a zero-trust, decoupled aesthetic, ensuring that client-facing boards and internal GFF administrators can configure, simulate, and audit multi-agent system states with total security and confidence.\n  6 | \n  7 | ---\n  8 | \n  9 | ## 1. Executive Narrative & Visual Metaphor\n 10 | \n 11 | ### 1.1. The \"Air-Gapped Cockpit\"\n 12 | To provide boards of directors and enterprise security teams with absolute risk containment, the GFF AI Portal operates on an architecture metaphor of the **Air-Gapped Cockpit**. Just as a sophisticated flight simulator provides full-fidelity interactive controls, telemetry streams, and compliance feedback without endangering actual aircraft, the GFF AI Frontend presents a secure operational layer completely decoupled from live production model executors and database kernels.\n 13 | \n 14 | ### 1.2. Key Visual Metaphors Built Into Phase 4\n 15 | *   **The Zero-Trust Handshake**: Visual block diagrams showing AES-256 session token pathways keeping client model parameters invisible to presentation networks.\n 16 | *   **Decoupled Model Enclaves**: Isolated hypervisor-reinforced boxes representing hardware-level execution tracking protected by hardware seed security boundaries.\n 17 | *   **The Living Terminal Feed**: Live, simulated eBPF-level diagnostic event streams flowing within the login page and route-guard modal, reinforcing the premium, high-tech engineering nature of GFF AI's systems.\n 18 | *   **Role Negotiation Selector**: A highly custom bypass console allowing engineers to simulate and toggle between 7 distinct enterprise roles in real time, inspecting permission-based modules dynamically.\n 19 | \n 20 | ---\n 21 | \n 22 | ## 2. Implemented Routes & Navigation Map\n 23 | \n 24 | Phase 4 includes a fully realized, responsive, and secure routing matrix built using Next.js App Router. These public and protected paths are structured into distinct areas of operational clearance:\n 25 | \n 26 | ### 2.1. Authentication Routes (Public Preview / Entrypoints)\n 27 | *   `/login` — Central unified login terminal, defaulting to Client Portal entry.\n 28 | *   `/portal/login` — Explicit Client Portal gateway.\n 29 | *   `/admin/login` — Explicit GFF Administration gateway, defaulting to GFF Administrator credentials.\n 30 | \n 31 | ### 2.2. Client Portal Routes (`/portal/*`)\n 32 | The Client Portal is tailored for executive control, tactical project management, and cost-governance audits.\n 33 | *   `/portal/dashboard` — Unified Executive Control & Enclave Telemetry overview.\n 34 | *   `/portal/projects` — Milestone and sandbox pipeline overview.\n 35 | *   `/portal/projects/[id]` — Deep-dive tracker for an individual multi-agent project pipeline.\n 36 | *   `/portal/ai-operations` — Configurator for active agent profiles, model configurations, and memory parameters.\n 37 | *   `/portal/ai-operations/[id]` — Deep-dive sandbox editor for a specific cognitive pipeline.\n 38 | *   `/portal/control-center` — Sovereign control hub for hardware deployment and orchestrator clusters.\n 39 | *   `/portal/governance` — Live policy tracking and ISO compliance auditing.\n 40 | *   `/portal/documents` — Secure Sovereign legal vault and document index.\n 41 | *   `/portal/documents/[id]` — Inline document audit and validation engine.\n 42 | *   `/portal/billing` — Chronological \"Computational Epoch\" cost ledger and summaries.\n 43 | *   `/portal/billing/invoices` — List of current and past cryptographically signed invoices.\n 44 | *   `/portal/billing/invoices/[id]` — PDF-like interactive view of invoice ledgers.\n 45 | *   `/portal/analytics` — Dynamic resource, token, and memory lane analytics grids.\n 46 | *   `/portal/support` — SLA ticket pipeline and live wire connection.\n 47 | *   `/portal/support/[id]` — SLA wire communication log with active system engineers.\n 48 | *   `/portal/settings` — Client workspace profiles, API keys, and notification bounds.\n 49 | *   `/portal/activity` — Session tracking logs and cryptographic handshakes.\n 50 | \n 51 | ### 2.3. Admin Oversight Console Routes (`/admin/*`)\n 52 | The Admin Portal is tailored for GFF staff to manage client accounts, monitor global compute load, and handle system governance.\n 53 | *   `/admin/dashboard` — Oversight Deck with Global Telemetry, Enclave Status, and active incidents.\n 54 | *   `/admin/clients` — Master directory of all enterprise client accounts.\n 55 | *   `/admin/clients/[id]` — Dynamic client profile, active contracts, and allocated computational resources.\n 56 | *   `/admin/projects` — Global sandbox scheduler and execution milestone pipelines.\n 57 | *   `/admin/projects/[id]` — Master pipeline control room.\n 58 | *   `/admin/ai-operations` — Global model deployment, latency logs, and prompt-injection safety controls.\n 59 | *   `/admin/governance` — Master ISO compliance rules manager and guardrail template builder.\n 60 | *   `/admin/documents` — Master contract vault and blueprint compiler.\n 61 | *   `/admin/billing` — Accounts receivable ledger, contract terms manager, and computational SLA auditing.\n 62 | *   `/admin/analytics` — Global network traffic, queue latency, and multi-region cluster efficiency.\n 63 | *   `/admin/support` — Master ticket dispatcher, operator assignment, and SLA countdowns.\n 64 | *   `/admin/users` — GFF staff roster and IAM permissions management.\n 65 | *   `/admin/settings` — Global configuration, hardware regions, and emergency system boundaries.\n 66 | *   `/admin/activity` — Audit stream tracking all administrative overrides and credential rotations.\n 67 | \n 68 | ---\n 69 | \n 70 | ## 3. High-Fidelity Local Preview Auth Behavior\n 71 | \n 72 | To fulfill the \"frontend-only placeholder\" guardrails while delivering a deeply interactive premium experience, Phase 4 implements an innovative client-side authentication engine.\n 73 | \n 74 | ```\n 75 | +-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 76 | |                            LOCAL PREVIEW AUTH ENGINE                              |\n 77 | |                                                                                   |\n 78 | |  1. Select Role Preset   -->   2. Auto-hydrate Mock Credentials                   |\n 79 | |  (Client Admin, etc.)          (Email, Cryptographic Salting logs)                |\n 80 | |                                                                                   |\n 81 | |  3. Trigger Handshake    -->   4. Simulate TLS Verification                       |\n 82 | |  (Password or OTP Auth)        (eBPF Terminal telemetry output animation)         |\n 83 | |                                                                                   |\n 84 | |  5. Store Session Key    -->   6. Redirect via Route Guard                        |\n 85 | |  (LocalStorage Cache)          (Enforces strict role permissions dynamically)     |\n 86 | +-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 87 | ```\n 88 | \n 89 | ### 3.1. Credentials vs. One-Time Password (OTP) Dual-Mode Login\n 90 | The `/login` screen offers users a seamless mechanism to explore enterprise access models:\n 91 | 1.  **Credentials Mode**: Classic password input with built-in telemetry simulation. As the user types their password, simulated SHA-512 salting processes stream to the active console terminal.\n 92 | 2.  **MFA OTP Mode**: Simulates a rotating 6-digit One-Time Password. To mimic state-of-the-art enterprise multi-factor authentication, an automatic 30-second countdown cycle triggers the generation of new temporary tokens with simulated cryptographic rotation logs.\n 93 | \n 94 | ### 3.2. Animated Telemetry Terminal Console\n 95 | A live scrolling diagnostics feed is built directly into the login card. It streams low-noise, technical operation logs in real time, mirroring hardware-level eBPF system calls:\n 96 | *   `[INIT] Handshake request received from node terminal.`\n 97 | *   `[IDENTITY] Resolved profile context: client_admin`\n 98 | *   `[SSL/TLS] Session handshake initiated via SHA-256 cipher.`\n 99 | *   `[CRYPT] Salted passphrase vector: SHA-512_SALT_F38C...`\n100 | *   `[SANDBOX] Memory enclave isolated. Sandbox state: READY.`","success":true}],"durationMs":3}}
